  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Despite leading cause of morbidity, treatment strategies for Rheumatic diseases are geared
      almost exclusively toward medical-pharmacological area away from offering the patient the
      possibility of an interdisciplinary approach to their disease.

      Present study test whether treatment of physiotherapy reduces stiffness and pain inherent in
      rheumatic disease and improve their quality of life related to health.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
